      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI directly maps to clinical hemolysis metric used in regulatory submission at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed from the power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle paths. NIH is the same metric reported in the predicate device 510(k) submission, enabling direct relative comparison via RH."
    },
