      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for Class II CPB application.",
      "rationale": "Formal use-error analysis not required at MRL 2. Simulation workflow executed by a single analyst with peer review of boundary condition setup and post-processing scripts. No automated use-error controls required at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection justified with reference to published validation evidence for hemolysis prediction in centrifugal pumps at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model selected based on published validation studies for centrifugal blood pumps. Turbulence modeled with SST k-omega; rotating reference frame with frozen-rotor interface. Model form limitations documented in the technical report appendix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs identified, sourced from traceable references, and uncertainty characterized at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis model coefficients (C=3.62e-5, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785) sourced from Giersiepen et al. (1990) with documented traceability. Blood viscosity modeled as Newtonian at 3.5 mPa·s based on measured hematocrit. A screening sensitivity study confirmed that ±10% variation in power-law coefficients produced less than 4% change in predicted NIH, supporting input adequacy."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
