    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2 for a Class II device with medium model influence. Validation evidence demonstrates NIH predictions within combined uncertainty bounds across the full CPB operating envelope. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all five operating points. A screening sensitivity study documented in the technical report confirmed low parametric sensitivity of NIH to hemolysis model coefficient variation, supporting confidence in the model inputs factor rating. The credibility assessment team unanimously accepts the simulation evidence as sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision.",
